detaileddescription.para: The only mandatory argument to this method is the uid. Everything else has (reasonably) sensible defaults.
Also, be aware that if you are searching backwards (i.e. end time > start time) then your results will be in reverse order. This is because results are generated on demand, not in advance.
This class now automatically swaps start/end and startaddr/endaddr if they are passed in reverse order. This is so we can avoid repeating all the reordering logic in higher level apps.

parameterdescription.para: IP Address of the records to find (0 for all records)
